(iii)	A)	Instructions to build and run the software

1)	Clone or download the project from GitHub.
2)	Open the project in Android Studio.
3)	We have been having issues building the Gradle, clone the repo and then using the "sync project with gradle files" has been working for us.
4)	For the VM use the pixel XL (API 26) with studio running Android 7.1.1 (Nougat) for the results we have shown in class.
5)	If the build will not run, we have experienced issues with "instant run" and might need to be disabled.

(iv)	b) Implemented functionalities.
1)	Create a calendar
2)	add in an event from month view with Title, date, start time, end time, occurrence (single, weekly, monthly), comments, and color.
3)	View events in a month view signified by colored dots for the dates with events.
4)	View events in an agenda view ordered in their start day and time.
5)	View events in a day view with more information in order of time.
6)	View a single event with all information including a delete and edit button
7)	Edit an event and all above attributes from add event, with ability to cancel edit leaving the original event intact.

